modules.description: Provides functions for decoding MPEG audio streams, including parsing headers, extracting sample data, and handling bitstream operations. Works with byte sequences, bitbuffers, and audio frame structures. Used to process MP3 files in multimedia applications and streaming services.

This module offers low-level MP3 decoding capabilities, including frame extraction, ID3 tag skipping, and position/time tracking, leveraging callbacks for stream manipulation. It processes audio data streams and metadata, supporting format inspection and precise control over decoding workflows. Use cases include media playback systems, audio analysis tools, and applications requiring direct interaction with MP3 file structures.
